Purpose
This file implements the planner agent.

Linear intent
1. Define local defaults for maximum plan length, confidence, and cost so the planner behavior is explicit.
2. Expose the agent id as `Planner`.
3. Define what counts as a text separator so raw user text can be split into rough planning segments.
4. Implement `extract_segments` to scan the input once, collect non-empty segments, and keep their original order.
5. Implement a small generic `take` helper to cap the number of produced plan steps.
6. Provide a fallback plan so the planner still returns a useful structure even when the input text gives no clean segments.
7. Implement `plan_from_text` to turn extracted segments into labeled stages like `Stage 1`, `Stage 2`, and `Stage 3`.
8. In `run`, accept only `Text` payloads because planning starts from raw request text.
9. Build a `Plan` payload from that text and attach planner-specific metrics and a short audit note.
10. Reject non-text payloads with a typed error payload instead of raising an exception.

